n: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">If you’re having trouble maintaining posture, use the handlebars, reduce the resistance, lower the incline level, or take a break if necessary.</span></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506862260" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670506862260"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">If You Feel Discomfort or Pain, Stop Exercising</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670506871769" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670506871769" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Remember to listen to your body.&nbsp;<span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">If you experience any pain or discomfort, you can try lowering exercise intensity by adjusting the machine.&nbsp;</span><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">If you’re still having issues, stop exercising and consult your doctor.</span></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670485569827" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670485569827" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-16737705